4:
An ambush?! How'd you pin me
down?
7:
So it was you... You're the one who
framed me for your crimes.
9:
Giselle?! Wh-what are you doing
here?!
11:
I should be asking you the same
question. Why would you sell cryptic
artifacts on the black market?!
14:
The only people who know about my
interests are a few acquaintances
and my old party members.
16:
But... I didn't want to believe any of
you would hurt me in such a way...
18:
D-damn you! I refuse to be caught
like this!
25:
You're under arrest for the illegal
smuggling of cryptic artifacts!
28:
Well, Giselle, it seems you can finally
put those smuggling accusations
behind you.
36:
I'm sure this journey has been an
arduous one. You did well.
39:
Yeah, and now it's time to celebrate
with drinks and grub.
42:
Thank you. None of this would have
been possible if you hadn't believed
in me and offered your support...
47:
By the way... Did you know him for
long?
51:
Yes... Indeed I did. I would say we
knew each other from the time we
both started out as adventurers.
53:
Ah, but our relationship was strictly
that of colleagues. Nothing more,
nothing less.
55:
Although it seemed to me that he
would have liked it to be more than
that...
63:
My party eventually disbanded, but I
had no reason to question the trust 
I had in them...
65:
But today... I saw a darkness in his
eyes that I'd never seen before...
66:
Did smuggling do that, or did it start
when he first learned about the
value of these dangerous items...
69:
Knowing their worth might've got
him scheming, but he's the one who
acted on those thoughts in the end.
71:
Or are you thinking you coulda
stopped him if you'd just done
something differently?
75:
Of course not. I doubt I held THAT
much sway over his life.
78:
It does make me a tad bit sad
though.
82: Giselle, thank goodness I found you!
87:
What do you mean, the seller you
arrested is dead?!
89:
W-we're just as shocked as you! We
were in the middle of our
interrogation when suddenly he
started acting strange!
91:
Wait, was someone trying to silence
him?!
94:
It's... possible. Perhaps they used
some sort of cryptic artifact as a
fail-safe.
97: How dare they... How DARE they!
104:
It seems my journey is not over after
all. Could I stay in Starview a little
longer?
108: Of course. Stay as long as you like.
114:
I will also continue to help with your
inspections of cryptic artifacts. Now,
could I ask for permission to use a
specific one?
117:
If the culprit used a cryptic artifact,
we may be able to trace it back to
the source...
126:
As long as we file the proper
paperwork afterward, it'll be fine. 
For now, do what you must.
132:
The enemy has had their fun. It's
about time we pay them back, don't
you agree?
135:
Indeed. I will make them regret the
day they decided to make me their
scapegoat.
139:
It's time to fight cryptic artifacts...
with cryptic artifacts!
